stepAnswer: There is a difference in the proportion of men and women that have at least one piercing
stepTitle: Joan Nguyen recently claimed that the proportion of college-age males with at least one pierced ear is as high as the proportion of college-age females. She conducted a survey in her classes. Out of 107 males, 20 had at least one pierced ear. Out of 92 females, 47 had at least one pierced ear. Do you believe that the proportion of males has reached the proportion of females?
choices: There is a difference in the proportion of men and women that have at least one piercing
